## What changed
Added missing macOS permissions required for Bonjour/mDNS LAN cluster discovery.

The ClusterKit module uses NWBrowser/NWListener with service type `_teale._tcp` for peer discovery, but the app bundle was missing the declarations macOS requires to allow this.

### Sources/InferencePoolApp/Info.plist
- Added `NSLocalNetworkUsageDescription` — privacy string shown when macOS prompts for local network access
- Added `NSBonjourServices` array with `_teale._tcp` — declares the Bonjour service type the app advertises/browses

### Sources/InferencePoolApp/InferencePool.entitlements
- Added `com.apple.developer.networking.multicast` — required for mDNS multicast traffic used by Bonjour

## Why
Two Macs on the same WiFi couldn't see each other in the Cluster view. The app had basic network.client/network.server entitlements but lacked Bonjour-specific permissions, so macOS silently blocked discovery.

## Impact
- Both machines need to rebuild with these changes for discovery to work
- Users will see a "Teale wants to find devices on your local network" prompt on first launch — must allow
- No code changes, only plist/entitlements configuration
